    "result": {"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"block":"learn-css-flexbox-by-building-a-photo-gallery","title":"Step 8","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Notice how the blue image border extends beyond the red gallery border. This is due to the way browsers calculate the size of container elements.</p>\n<p>The <code>box-sizing</code> property is used to set this behavior. By default, the <code>content-box</code> model is used. With this model, when an element has a specific width, that width is calculated based only on the element's content. Padding and border values get added to the total width, so the element grows to accommodate these values.</p>\n<p>Try setting <code>box-sizing</code> to <code>content-box</code> explicitly, with the global <code>*</code> selector. At this point, you will not see any changes, because you are using the default value.</p>\n</section>","id":"6494da0daf5df5197963671d","hasEditableBoundaries":true,"instructions":null,"notes":null,"challengeType":0,"helpCategory":"HTML-CSS","videoUrl":null,"superBlock":"2022/responsive-web-design","translationPending":false,"forumTopicId":null,"fields":{"blockName":"learn-css-flexbox-by-building-a-photo-gallery","slug":"/learn/2022/responsive-web-design/learn-css-flexbox-by-building-a-photo-gallery/step-8","tests":[{"text":"<p>You should have a <code>*</code> selector.</p>","testString":"assert.exists(new __helpers.CSSHelp(document).getStyle('*'));"},{"text":"<p>Your <code>*</code> selector should have a <code>box-sizing</code> property.</p>","testString":"assert.exists(new __helpers.CSSHelp(document).getStyle('*')?.boxSizing);"},{"text":"<p>Your <code>*</code> selector should have its <code>box-sizing</code> property set to <code>content-box</code>.</p>","testString":"assert.equal(new __helpers.CSSHelp(document).getStyle('*')?.boxSizing, 'content-box');"}]},"required":[],"usesMultifileEditor":true,"challengeFiles":[{"fileKey":"indexhtml","ext":"html","name":"index","contents":"<!DO